## DRY Principle

### When to extract
Three or more occurrences of the same logic → extract.

### Examples
```ts
// WRONG: duplicated date formatting
const date1 = new Date(ts1).toLocaleDateString('en-GB');
const date2 = new Date(ts2).toLocaleDateString('en-GB');

// CORRECT: extracted utility
export function formatDate(timestamp: number): string {
  return new Date(timestamp).toLocaleDateString('en-GB');
}
```

```tsx
// WRONG: copy-pasted button styles
<button className="bg-indigo-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded hover:bg-indigo-700">Save</button>
<button className="bg-indigo-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded hover:bg-indigo-700">Submit</button>

// CORRECT: reusable component
function PrimaryButton({ children, ...props }: ButtonProps) {
  return <button className="bg-indigo-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded hover:bg-indigo-700" {...props}>{children}</button>;
}
```

### What DRY is NOT
DRY is about knowledge, not code similarity.
Two similar functions that solve different problems should NOT be merged.

### Checklist
- [ ] No logic duplicated 3+ times
- [ ] Shared utilities in `src/lib/` or `src/utils/`
- [ ] Reusable components in `src/components/ui/`
- [ ] Custom hooks abstract shared stateful logic

## Separation of Concerns

### Three Layers
| Layer | Technology | Responsibility |
|-------|-----------|---------------|
| Structure | HTML | Content and semantics |
| Presentation | CSS | Visual appearance |
| Behaviour | JavaScript | Interaction and logic |

### Anti-patterns
```html
<!-- WRONG: behaviour in HTML -->
<button onclick="document.getElementById('modal').style.display='block'">Open</button>

<!-- WRONG: style in JS -->
element.style.backgroundColor = 'red';
element.style.fontSize = '14px';

<!-- WRONG: logic in template -->
<div>{{ user.firstName[0].toUpperCase() + user.firstName.slice(1) }}</div>
```

### Correct patterns
```html
<!-- Structure: semantic HTML -->
<button class="btn-primary" data-action="open-modal" data-target="contact-modal">Open</button>
```
```css
/* Presentation: CSS classes */
.btn-primary { background: var(--color-accent); color: white; }
.modal[aria-hidden="false"] { display: block; }
```
```js
// Behaviour: JS handles interaction via class/attribute toggle
document.querySelectorAll('[data-action]').forEach(btn => {
  btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
    const target = document.getElementById(btn.dataset.target);
    target.setAttribute('aria-hidden', 'false');
  });
});
```

### In React
Use `className` for visual state, not inline styles.
Extract display logic to utility functions, not JSX.

### Checklist
- [ ] No inline style attributes (except dynamic values from JS)
- [ ] No onclick/onchange in HTML attributes
- [ ] Visual state communicated via CSS classes or data attributes
- [ ] Display logic extracted to utility functions

## Write Code to Be Read

### Naming: intent over brevity
```ts
// WRONG
const d = new Date();
const arr = users.filter(u => u.a);

// CORRECT
const createdAt = new Date();
const activeUsers = users.filter(user => user.isActive);
```

### Functions: single responsibility
```ts
// WRONG: does too much
function processUser(user) {
  validateEmail(user.email);
  const hashed = bcrypt.hash(user.password);
  db.save({ ...user, password: hashed });
  sendWelcomeEmail(user.email);
  analytics.track('user_created', user.id);
}

// CORRECT: split into focused functions
async function registerUser(user: NewUser): Promise<User> {
  const validated = validateUser(user);
  const saved = await persistUser(validated);
  await notifyUserCreated(saved);
  return saved;
}
```

### Avoid clever code
```ts
// WRONG: clever but unreadable
const result = arr.reduce((a, b) => ({...a, [b.id]: b}), {});

// CORRECT: readable
const usersById: Record<string, User> = {};
for (const user of arr) {
  usersById[user.id] = user;
}
```

### Early return over nesting
```ts
// WRONG: pyramid of doom
function getDiscount(user) {
  if (user) {
    if (user.isPremium) {
      if (user.loyaltyYears > 5) { return 0.3; }
    }
  }
  return 0;
}

// CORRECT: early return
function getDiscount(user: User | null): number {
  if (!user) return 0;
  if (!user.isPremium) return 0;
  if (user.loyaltyYears > 5) return 0.3;
  return 0;
}
```

### Checklist
- [ ] Variables named for intent, not type
- [ ] Functions < 50 lines, single responsibility
- [ ] No nesting > 4 levels
- [ ] No clever one-liners that need a comment to explain

## Commenting Guidelines

### Rule: Comment the WHY, not the WHAT

```ts
// WRONG: describes what the code does (obvious from reading it)
// Increment counter by 1
counter++;

// WRONG: restates the function name
// Get user by ID
function getUserById(id: string) { ... }

// CORRECT: explains a non-obvious reason
// Delay 200ms to avoid race condition with auth cookie being set
await sleep(200);
const session = await getSession();

// CORRECT: explains a business rule not derivable from code
// EU users get 14-day trial (GDPR Article 17 compliance)
const trialDays = user.region === 'EU' ? 14 : 7;

// CORRECT: explains a workaround for a known bug
// Safari 15 returns undefined for navigator.userAgentData — use UA string fallback
const isMobile = navigator.userAgentData?.mobile ?? /Mobi/.test(navigator.userAgent);
```

### When to add a comment
- Hidden constraint or external requirement
- Subtle invariant or ordering dependency
- Workaround for a specific third-party bug
- Counter-intuitive algorithm choice (with performance rationale)

### When NOT to add a comment
- Describing what the code clearly does
- Restating the function/variable name
- TODOs without a ticket number or owner
- Commented-out code (delete it; use git)

### Checklist
- [ ] No comments that describe the WHAT
- [ ] No commented-out code blocks
- [ ] TODOs reference a ticket: `// TODO(#234): remove after migration`
- [ ] Every remaining comment explains WHY

## CSS Preprocessor Best Practices

### SASS Structure
```scss
// _variables.scss — design tokens
$color-accent: #6366f1;
$font-body: 'Inter', sans-serif;
$space-4: 1rem;

// _mixins.scss — reusable patterns
@mixin flex-center {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
}

@mixin respond-to($breakpoint) {
  @if $breakpoint == 'md' { @media (min-width: 768px) { @content; } }
  @if $breakpoint == 'lg' { @media (min-width: 1024px) { @content; } }
}

// component.scss
.card {
  padding: $space-4;

  &__title { font-weight: 700; }
  &__body { color: $color-muted; }

  @include respond-to('md') { display: grid; }
}
```

### Nesting depth limit: 3 levels
```scss
// WRONG: 5 levels deep
.nav .nav__list .nav__item .nav__link:hover span { color: red; }

// CORRECT: max 3
.nav__link {
  &:hover { color: $color-accent; }
  span { display: inline-block; }
}
```

### Checklist
- [ ] Variables defined in `_variables.scss` (tokens, not magic numbers)
- [ ] Nesting depth ≤ 3
- [ ] No SCSS compiled output in version control
- [ ] Mixins for repeated patterns, not copy-paste

## CSS Global vs Local Separation

### Global styles (load once)
```css
/* styles/global.css */
*, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; }
body { margin: 0; font-family: var(--font-body); }
a { color: inherit; }
img, video { max-width: 100%; display: block; }
```

### Design tokens (global)
```css
/* styles/tokens.css */
:root {
  --color-accent: oklch(65% 0.2 250);
  --space-4: 1rem;
  --radius-md: 0.5rem;
}
```

### Component styles — CSS Modules (React)
```tsx
// Button.module.css
.root { padding: 0.5rem 1rem; border-radius: var(--radius-md); }
.primary { background: var(--color-accent); }

// Button.tsx
import styles from './Button.module.css';
export function Button({ variant = 'primary' }) {
  return <button className={`${styles.root} ${styles[variant]}`}>...</button>;
}
```

### Load order
1. `tokens.css` — CSS custom properties
2. `global.css` — resets and base styles
3. Component module CSS — scoped styles

### Checklist
- [ ] Global styles limited to reset + tokens
- [ ] Component styles in .module.css or BEM-namespaced
- [ ] No generic class names (`.container`, `.wrapper`) in global CSS
- [ ] No `!important` in component CSS

## CSS Browser Rendering — Right-to-Left Matching

### How browsers match selectors
```css
.nav .nav__link span { color: red; }
```
Browser does:
1. Find ALL `<span>` elements on the page
2. Check if parent is `.nav__link`
3. Check if ancestor is `.nav`

→ Step 1 scans every span. Large DOM = slow.

### Optimization: use BEM / scoped classes
```css
/* WRONG: broad key selector */
.nav ul li a { color: var(--color-accent); }

/* CORRECT: scoped key selector — browser resolves .nav__link fast */
.nav__link { color: var(--color-accent); }
.nav__link--active { color: var(--color-primary); }
```

### Avoid universal key selector in chains
```css
/* WRONG: * is the key selector — matches every element first */
.container > * { margin-bottom: 1rem; }

/* BETTER: use direct child class or :where() */
.container > .flow-child { margin-bottom: 1rem; }
/* or */
.container > :not(:last-child) { margin-bottom: 1rem; }
```

### Checklist
- [ ] No deeply nested descendant selectors (avoid > 2 levels)
- [ ] Key selectors (rightmost) are specific class names, not elements
- [ ] No universal `*` as key selector in chains
- [ ] CSS profiler checked for slow selectors if paint time > 16ms

## CSS Methodology

### BEM Naming (Block__Element--Modifier)
```css
/* Block */
.card { ... }

/* Element (part of block) */
.card__title { ... }
.card__body { ... }
.card__footer { ... }

/* Modifier (state or variant) */
.card--featured { ... }
.card--disabled { ... }
.card__title--large { ... }
```

### ITCSS File Organization
```
src/styles/
  1-settings/   # tokens, variables
  2-tools/      # mixins, functions
  3-generic/    # normalize, reset
  4-elements/   # bare HTML elements
  5-objects/    # layout patterns (no cosmetics)
  6-components/ # UI components
  7-utilities/  # single-purpose helpers
```

### OOCSS Principles
1. Separate structure from skin
2. Separate container from content
```css
/* Structure (reusable layout) */
.media { display: flex; gap: 1rem; }
/* Skin (visual style) */
.media--bordered { border: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
```

### Pick ONE methodology
Don't mix BEM with utility-first in the same component.
If using Tailwind: utility-first everywhere; BEM only for JS-toggled states.

### Checklist
- [ ] Methodology documented in CONTRIBUTING.md
- [ ] All components follow same naming pattern
- [ ] No mixing of methodologies in same file
- [ ] Linter enforces methodology (stylelint-plugin-bem)

## Design System & CSS Variables

### Token Definition
```css
:root {
  /* Color */
  --color-primary: oklch(65% 0.2 250);
  --color-surface: oklch(98% 0 0);
  --color-text: oklch(15% 0 0);
  --color-muted: oklch(55% 0 0);
  --color-border: oklch(85% 0 0);
  --color-error: oklch(55% 0.22 25);

  /* Typography */
  --text-xs: 0.75rem;   /* 12px */
  --text-sm: 0.875rem;  /* 14px */
  --text-base: 1rem;    /* 16px */
  --text-lg: 1.125rem;  /* 18px */
  --text-xl: 1.25rem;   /* 20px */
  --text-2xl: 1.5rem;   /* 24px */

  /* Spacing (4px grid) */
  --space-1: 0.25rem;   --space-2: 0.5rem;
  --space-3: 0.75rem;   --space-4: 1rem;
  --space-6: 1.5rem;    --space-8: 2rem;
  --space-12: 3rem;     --space-16: 4rem;

  /* Radius */
  --radius-sm: 0.25rem;
  --radius-md: 0.5rem;
  --radius-lg: 1rem;
  --radius-full: 9999px;

  /* Elevation */
  --shadow-sm: 0 1px 2px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.05);
  --shadow-md: 0 4px 6px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.1);
  --shadow-lg: 0 10px 15px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.1);
}
```

### Dark mode via token override
```css
@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
  :root {
    --color-surface: oklch(15% 0 0);
    --color-text: oklch(95% 0 0);
    --color-border: oklch(25% 0 0);
  }
}
```

### Checklist
- [ ] All colors reference CSS variables, never hardcoded hex
- [ ] All spacing from scale (not arbitrary px)
- [ ] Typography uses token scale
- [ ] Dark mode works via token override only
- [ ] Design system documented for team

## CSS Animation Performance

### Rendering Pipeline
```
JS → Style → Layout → Paint → Composite
```
Animating layout properties triggers full pipeline. Compositor properties skip to Composite.

### Compositor-safe (60fps)
```css
/* CORRECT: only composite-layer properties */
.fade { transition: opacity 300ms ease; }
.slide { transition: transform 300ms ease-out; }
.reveal { transition: clip-path 400ms ease, opacity 400ms ease; }
.blur { transition: filter 200ms ease; }
```

### Layout-thrashing (causes jank)
```css
/* WRONG: triggers layout on every frame */
.animate { transition: width 300ms; }     /* layout */
.animate { transition: height 300ms; }    /* layout */
.animate { transition: top 300ms; }       /* layout */
.animate { transition: margin 300ms; }    /* layout */
.animate { transition: padding 300ms; }   /* layout */
.animate { transition: font-size 300ms; } /* layout */
```

### Slide-in pattern (no layout thrash)
```css
/* Simulate width expand without animating width */
.drawer {
  transform: translateX(-100%);
  transition: transform 300ms ease-out;
}
.drawer--open { transform: translateX(0); }
```

### will-change (use sparingly)
```css
/* Only on elements about to animate */
.will-animate { will-change: transform, opacity; }
/* Remove after animation: */
.animated { will-change: auto; }
```

### Checklist
- [ ] No transitions on width/height/top/left/margin/padding
- [ ] Animations use transform + opacity only
- [ ] `will-change` set only on elements actively animating
- [ ] Chrome DevTools Performance tab shows no layout/paint drops

## Don't Remove outline — Style It

### WCAG 2.4.7 (Level AA)
All keyboard-operable elements must have a visible focus indicator.

### WRONG: removes focus for everyone
```css
* { outline: none; }           /* CRITICAL violation */
button:focus { outline: 0; }   /* CRITICAL violation */
a:focus { outline: none; }     /* CRITICAL violation */
```

### CORRECT: style :focus-visible (not :focus)
```css
/* Only shows for keyboard navigation, not mouse click */
:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid var(--color-accent);
  outline-offset: 2px;
  border-radius: 2px;
}

/* Or a high-contrast ring */
:focus-visible {
  box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px rgb(99 102 241 / 0.5);
  outline: 2px solid #6366f1;
  outline-offset: 2px;
}
```

### Component-level focus styling
```css
.btn:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid var(--color-accent);
  outline-offset: 3px;
}

.input:focus-visible {
  border-color: var(--color-accent);
  box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px rgb(99 102 241 / 0.2);
  outline: none; /* OK — replaced by border + shadow */
}
```

### Audit command
```bash
grep -rn 'outline.*none\|outline.*0' src/styles/ --include='*.css' --include='*.scss'
```

### Checklist
- [ ] Zero `outline: none` without a visible replacement
- [ ] All interactive elements have `:focus-visible` style
- [ ] Focus indicator meets 3:1 contrast ratio against adjacent color
- [ ] Keyboard tab order matches visual order

## Responsive & Fluid Styling

### Mobile-First Breakpoints
```css
/* Base styles = mobile */
.grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 1rem; }

/* Progressively enhance */
@media (min-width: 640px)  { .grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); } }
@media (min-width: 1024px) { .grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); } }
@media (min-width: 1280px) { .grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr); } }
```

### Fluid Layout without media queries
```css
/* Auto-fit grid: fills with as many columns as fit */
.card-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(min(280px, 100%), 1fr));
  gap: clamp(1rem, 3vw, 2rem);
}
```

### Fluid Container
```css
.container {
  width: min(100% - 2rem, 1200px);
  margin-inline: auto;
}
```

### Fluid Typography
```css
:root {
  --text-hero: clamp(2rem, 1.5rem + 4vw, 5rem);
  --text-body: clamp(0.875rem, 0.8rem + 0.3vw, 1rem);
}
```

### Breakpoint reference
| Name | Min-width | Targets |
|------|-----------|---------|
| sm | 640px | Large phones landscape |
| md | 768px | Tablets |
| lg | 1024px | Laptops |
| xl | 1280px | Desktops |
| 2xl | 1536px | Wide screens |

### Checklist
- [ ] Mobile-first: base styles work at 320px
- [ ] No fixed widths that break at small screens
- [ ] Fluid typography with clamp()
- [ ] Tested at 320, 375, 768, 1024, 1440
- [ ] No horizontal overflow at any breakpoint
- [ ] Touch targets >= 44x44px

## Font Loading Strategy

### Rules
- Max 2 font families (3 if there's a monospace for code)
- Preload only the weight/style used above the fold
- Always use `font-display: swap`
- Subset to Latin characters if global audience not needed

### HTML: preload critical font
```html
<head>
  <!-- Preload only what's needed for above-fold render -->
  <link rel="preload" href="/fonts/inter-400.woff2" as="font" type="font/woff2" crossorigin>
  <link rel="preload" href="/fonts/inter-700.woff2" as="font" type="font/woff2" crossorigin>
</head>
```

### CSS: @font-face setup
```css
@font-face {
  font-family: 'Inter';
  src: url('/fonts/inter-400.woff2') format('woff2');
  font-weight: 400;
  font-style: normal;
  font-display: swap; /* show system font while loading; swap when ready */
}

@font-face {
  font-family: 'Inter';
  src: url('/fonts/inter-700.woff2') format('woff2');
  font-weight: 700;
  font-style: normal;
  font-display: swap;
}
```

### Prevent CLS from font swap
```css
/* Size-adjust reduces layout shift when system font swaps to custom */
@font-face {
  font-family: 'FallbackInter';
  src: local('Arial');
  size-adjust: 107%;  /* match Inter's metrics */
}
body { font-family: 'Inter', 'FallbackInter', sans-serif; }
```

### Self-host vs CDN
Prefer self-hosting — eliminates DNS lookup, CORS, and privacy concerns.

### Checklist
- [ ] Max 2 font families loaded
- [ ] Critical font weights preloaded in `<head>`
- [ ] `font-display: swap` on all @font-face declarations
- [ ] Font files are woff2 format
- [ ] CLS score < 0.1 (measure after font load)

## Minimize & Validate CSS

### PostCSS Setup
```js
// postcss.config.js
module.exports = {
  plugins: [
    require('autoprefixer'),          // vendor prefixes
    require('cssnano')({ preset: 'default' }), // minify
    // PurgeCSS handled by Tailwind or separately
  ]
};
```

### PurgeCSS (standalone)
```js
// purgecss.config.js
module.exports = {
  content: ['./src/**/*.{html,tsx,ts,jsx,js}'],
  css: ['./dist/styles.css'],
  safelist: [
    // Classes added dynamically by JS — must safelist or they'll be purged
    /^is-/,
    /^has-/,
    'active', 'open', 'visible'
  ]
};
```

### Tailwind: built-in purge
```js
// tailwind.config.ts
export default {
  content: ['./src/**/*.{ts,tsx}'],
  // automatically removes unused utilities
};
```

### CSS Validation
```bash
# Check for syntax errors
npx stylelint 'src/**/*.css' 'src/**/*.scss'

# W3C validator (CI)
npx css-validator dist/styles.css
```

### Production checks
```bash
# Measure CSS size
wc -c dist/styles.css
# After gzip:
gzip -c dist/styles.css | wc -c
```

### Checklist
- [ ] Autoprefixer in PostCSS pipeline
- [ ] CSS minified in production build
- [ ] PurgeCSS or Tailwind removes unused styles
- [ ] Dynamically-added classes in PurgeCSS safelist
- [ ] Stylelint runs in CI

## Explicit Transition Properties

### Rule: never use `transition: all`

```css
/* WRONG: triggers on any property change — expensive */
.card { transition: all 0.3s ease; }

/* CORRECT: specify exactly what transitions */
.card { transition: transform 200ms ease-out, box-shadow 200ms ease-out; }
```

### Why `transition: all` is harmful
1. Browser must monitor ALL properties for changes
2. Adding a new property (even unintentionally) triggers animation
3. Layout properties accidentally become animated → jank
4. Color and opacity properties get mixed with layout → inconsistent

### Practical examples
```css
/* Button: only color and shadow change on hover */
.btn {
  transition:
    background-color 150ms ease,
    border-color 150ms ease,
    box-shadow 150ms ease;
}

/* Card lift effect */
.card {
  transition:
    transform 200ms ease-out,
    box-shadow 200ms ease-out;
}
.card:hover {
  transform: translateY(-4px);
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);
}

/* Link underline */
.link {
  transition: color 150ms ease, text-decoration-color 150ms ease;
}
```

### Checklist
- [ ] Zero `transition: all` in codebase
- [ ] Every transition names specific properties
- [ ] Transitioning only compositor-safe properties (no width/height/top)
- [ ] Transition duration < 400ms for UI micro-interactions

## Avoid Constantly Overwriting Styles

### Pattern to avoid
```css
/* Sets red, then overrides to blue — why set red at all? */
.btn { color: red; }
.btn.primary { color: blue; }
.btn.secondary { color: green; }
.btn.disabled { color: gray; }
```

### Root cause: missing variant system
If you set a base value then always override it, the base is wrong.

### CORRECT: variants instead of overrides
```css
/* Base: structural only — no color commitment */
.btn {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  padding: var(--space-2) var(--space-4);
  border-radius: var(--radius-md);
  font-weight: 500;
  cursor: pointer;
  /* No color here — variants own color */
}

/* Variants: own their full appearance */
.btn--primary { background: var(--color-accent); color: white; }
.btn--secondary { background: transparent; border: 1px solid var(--color-accent); color: var(--color-accent); }
.btn--ghost { background: transparent; color: var(--color-text); }

/* States modify variants */
.btn:disabled { opacity: 0.5; cursor: not-allowed; }
```

### Check for overwrite smell
```bash
# Find rules that set a property then another rule overrides it at same specificity
# Manual inspection: look for duplicated property names in selector groups
grep -A 5 '^\.btn' src/styles/components.css | grep -E '^\s+color:'
```

### Checklist
- [ ] Base classes set structure only (size, flex, grid)
- [ ] Color/typography owned by variant modifiers
- [ ] No property set in base and immediately overridden in modifier
- [ ] Variant approach documented for team

## Utility Classes

### When to create a utility
Pattern repeated in 3+ places → extract to utility class.

```css
/* Pattern: flex + center — repeated everywhere */
.flex-center {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
}

/* Pattern: visually hidden (accessibility) */
.sr-only {
  position: absolute;
  width: 1px;
  height: 1px;
  padding: 0;
  margin: -1px;
  overflow: hidden;
  clip: rect(0, 0, 0, 0);
  white-space: nowrap;
  border-width: 0;
}

/* Pattern: truncate long text */
.truncate {
  overflow: hidden;
  text-overflow: ellipsis;
  white-space: nowrap;
}

/* Pattern: interactive overlay overlay */
.overlay-hover {
  position: relative;
  isolation: isolate;
}
.overlay-hover::after {
  content: '';
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;
  background: currentColor;
  opacity: 0;
  transition: opacity 150ms;
  border-radius: inherit;
}
.overlay-hover:hover::after { opacity: 0.08; }
```

### Tailwind: utility-first by design
With Tailwind, utilities are generated. Create components via `@apply` for repeated multi-class patterns:
```css
@layer components {
  .btn-base {
    @apply inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-md font-medium transition-colors;
  }
}
```

### Checklist
- [ ] Utilities documented in `styles/utilities.css`
- [ ] No duplicate pattern in 3+ places
- [ ] Utility names describe what they do, not how they look
- [ ] `sr-only` utility always available for accessibility

## Box Sizing Reset

### Always include in global reset
```css
/*
  The box-sizing reset.
  Apply to everything including pseudo-elements.
*/
*, *::before, *::after {
  box-sizing: border-box;
}
```

### Why it matters
```css
/* Without border-box: */
.box {
  width: 200px;
  padding: 20px;
  border: 2px solid;
}
/* Actual width = 200 + 20 + 20 + 2 + 2 = 244px — surprise! */

/* With border-box: */
.box {
  box-sizing: border-box;
  width: 200px;
  padding: 20px;
  border: 2px solid;
}
/* Actual width = 200px — padding and border included */
```

### Opt-out pattern (for third-party widgets)
```css
*, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; }

/* Opt-out third-party component back to content-box */
.third-party-widget, .third-party-widget * {
  box-sizing: content-box;
}
```

### Checklist
- [ ] `*, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; }` in global reset
- [ ] Reset loaded before all component styles
- [ ] No component explicitly sets `box-sizing: content-box` unless needed for third-party compatibility

